olive oil
1 packet beef mince
½ sachet Garlic & Herb Seasoning
1 packet garlic paste
1 bag baby spinach leaves
1 box tomato sugo
1 packet spinach & ricotta tortellini
1 cucumber
1 bag Rocket leaves
½ bottle Balsamic & Olive Oil Dressing
1 bag parsley

• Boil the kettle
• Heat olive oil in a frying pan over high
heat
• Cook beef, breaking up with a spoon,
until browned, 3-4 mins
• Stir in seasoning (1/2 sachet for 2P
/ 1 sachet for 4P), garlic paste and
spinach and cook until wilted,
1-2 mins
• Stir through sugo. Remove from heat

• Half-fill a saucepan with boiling water
• Bring to the boil over high heat, then
add tortellini and cook until ‘al dente’,
3 mins
• Using a slotted spoon, transfer
tortellini to the frying pan along with
a dash of pasta water
• Toss to combine, then season

• Thinly slice cucumber
• In a bowl, combine cucumber,
rocket and balsamic dressing (1/2
bottle for 2P / 1 bottle for 4P)
• Toss and season to taste
• Serve beef ragu and tortellini with
salad and torn parsley leaves